  <summary>1/21/1987--Introduced.
Repeals the provisions of the Internal Revenue Code which include one-half of social security and tier 1 railroad retirement benefits in the gross income of the taxpayer. Provides that one-half of social security benefits paid to nonresident aliens is includible in the gross income of the nonresident alien.</summary>
